{"pageProps":{"title":"Illocutionary act - Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia","hast":{"type":"root","children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"dl","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"dt","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"url"}]},{"type":"element","tagName":"dd","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Illocutionary_act"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Illocutionary_act"}]}]}]},{"type":"element","tagName":"blockquote","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"The concept of illocutionary acts was introduced into perlocutionary act "},{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Linguistics"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Linguistics"}]},{"type":"text","value":"][linguistics]] by the philosopher "},{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/John_L._Austin"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"John L. Austin"}]},{"type":"text","value":" in his investigation of the various aspects of "},{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Speech_acts"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"speech acts"}]},{"type":"text","value":". In Austin's framework, locution is what was said, illocution is what was meant, and perlocution is what happened as a result. For example, when somebody says \"Is there any salt?\" at the dinner table, the illocutionary act (the meaning conveyed) is effectively \"please give me some salt\" even though the "},{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Locutionary_act"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"locutionary act"}]},{"type":"text","value":" (the literal sentence) was to ask a question about the presence of salt. The [["},{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Perlocutionary_act"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Perlocutionary_act"}]},{"type":"text","value":" (the actual effect), was to cause somebody to hand over the salt.\n"}]}]}]},"filetags":":languages:games:","backlinks":[{"path":"/all_pages","title":"All Pages"}]},"__N_SSG":true}